'''''Lucrezia Borgia''''' (Spanish:'''''Lucrecia Borgia''''') is a 1947 Argentine [[historical film]] directed by [[Luis Bayón Herrera]] and starring [[Olinda Bozán]], [[Héctor Quintanilla (actor)|Héctor Quintanilla]] and [[Gogó Andreu]].<ref>Gillespie, Engel & Dieterle p.689</ref> The film portrays the life of [[Lucrezia Borgia]] (1480-1519).

The film's sets were designed by the [[art director]] [[Juan Manuel Concado]].

